    "Later on, Liang et al. [21] proposed a vision-based marker less pose estimation framework for articulated construction robots.",
    "The authors used, a stacked hourglass deep neural network to estimate the joint locations for an articulated robot.",
    "The concept is similar to human pose estimation but it has been used to extract the joint information of articulated robots.",
    "Cai et al. [22] discussed a patient's upper limb motion tracking using a Kinect depth camera with VICON markers.",
    "The Barret WAM manipulator is used to track the patient's upper limb movement for the rehabilitation exercise."
